{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_130","type":"agent_message","text":"Implemented the first simulator-facing skeleton-neuron path end to end.\n\n**Changed**\n- Added a canonical deterministic skeleton runtime asset bundle in [src/flywire_wave/skeleton_runtime_assets.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/skeleton_runtime_assets.py#L20). It materializes `skeleton_runtime_asset.v1` from cached SWC, stores a mass-normalized skeleton graph operator plus node order/mass/readout semantics, and rejects invalid or scientifically unsupported inputs with explicit errors at [src/flywire_wave/skeleton_runtime_assets.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/skeleton_runtime_assets.py#L113) and [src/flywire_wave/skeleton_runtime_assets.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/skeleton_runtime_assets.py#L170).\n- Extended the morphology contract and planner so `skeleton_neuron` now requires `skeleton_runtime_asset`, mixed-fidelity plans discover it deterministically, and missing assets fail clearly instead of degrading. See [src/flywire_wave/hybrid_morphology_contract.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/hybrid_morphology_contract.py#L106), [src/flywire_wave/simulation_planning.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/simulation_planning.py#L1930), [src/flywire_wave/simulation_planning.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/simulation_planning.py#L2142), [src/flywire_wave/simulation_planning.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/simulation_planning.py#L2655), and [src/flywire_wave/simulation_planning.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/simulation_planning.py#L2840).\n- Implemented the deterministic skeleton state container and mixed surface+skeleton runtime adapter in [src/flywire_wave/hybrid_morphology_runtime.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/hybrid_morphology_runtime.py#L193), [src/flywire_wave/hybrid_morphology_runtime.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/hybrid_morphology_runtime.py#L576), and [src/flywire_wave/hybrid_morphology_runtime.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/hybrid_morphology_runtime.py#L731). It supports zero/init state, source injection, shared stepping, readout export, and coupling projection for skeleton roots using only local cached artifacts. Selected-edge execution touching skeleton roots now fails explicitly until FW-M11-006 at [src/flywire_wave/hybrid_morphology_runtime.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/hybrid_morphology_runtime.py#L1048).\n- Documented the runtime handoff in [docs/hybrid_morphology_design.md](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/docs/hybrid_morphology_design.md#L63).\n\n**Verified**\n- `make test` passed: 137 tests, all green.\n- Focused skeleton verification passed: `python3 -m unittest -v tests.test_hybrid_morphology_runtime.HybridMorphologyRuntimeTest.test_skeleton_runtime_asset_materialization_is_deterministic tests.test_hybrid_morphology_runtime.HybridMorphologyRuntimeTest.test_surface_skeleton_runtime_adapter_runs_supported_mixed_fixture_deterministically`\n- Added regression coverage for contract/planner/runtime behavior in [tests/test_hybrid_morphology_contract.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/tests/test_hybrid_morphology_contract.py#L119), [tests/test_simulation_planning.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/p